# Git Workflow

- Before changing code, create a focused branch from the latest local `master`.
- Never commit feature or fix work directly to `master`.
- After verification, update the changelog when the change is user-visible.
- Commit the completed work with the repository's commit-message style.
- Push the feature branch to `origin` and set its upstream.
- Never force-push `master`.
